<paragraph blockId="20.[826,1442,1388,1533]" pageId="20" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis box="[826,952,1388,1409]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="40">Etymology:</emphasis>
The specific name is a noun in apposition and dedicated to arachnologist Jorge Iván Mendoza Marroquín for his participation in collecting the 
<typeStatus box="[1392,1441,1450,1471]" pageId="20" pageNumber="40">type</typeStatus>
series, and his contribution to knowledge of the spiders of 
<collectingCountry box="[856,939,1511,1533]" name="Mexico" pageId="20" pageNumber="40">Mexico</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[826,1441,1573,1810]" pageId="20" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis box="[826,944,1574,1595]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="40">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Valdez-Mondragón &amp; Francke" authorityYear="2015" box="[1081,1191,1573,1595]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Ixchela" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="20" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tlayuda">
<emphasis box="[1081,1191,1573,1595]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="40">I. tlayuda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but distinguished by the FAC long and rounded, forming an angle of 90° with the chelicerae in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1243,1324,1635,1657]" captionStart="Figures 56–67" captionStartId="15.[144,234,1760,1779]" captionTargetBox="[270,1296,202,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-0@15.[263,1305,194,1730]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 56–67. Ixchela mendozai sp. nov. Male: 56, 57, Habitus, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. 58, Carapace and chelicerae, frontal view. 59, Chelicerae, frontal view. 60, 61, Left palp, retrolateral and prolateral views, respectively. 62, Chelicera, lateral view. 63, Bulb and embolus, prolatero-dorsal view (arrow indicates the curved and sharp subdistally sclerotized spine). Female: 64, Epigynum, ventral view. 65, Epigynum, dorsal view. 66, Epigynum, left lateral view. 67, Epigynum, frontal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs 58, 59, 62–67), 1 mm (Figs 56, 57, 60, 61)." pageId="20" pageNumber="40">Fig. 62</figureCitation>
); the VAF with sharp tip (
<figureCitation box="[1016,1097,1665,1687]" captionStart="Figures 56–67" captionStartId="15.[144,234,1760,1779]" captionTargetBox="[270,1296,202,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-0@15.[263,1305,194,1730]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 56–67. Ixchela mendozai sp. nov. Male: 56, 57, Habitus, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. 58, Carapace and chelicerae, frontal view. 59, Chelicerae, frontal view. 60, 61, Left palp, retrolateral and prolateral views, respectively. 62, Chelicera, lateral view. 63, Bulb and embolus, prolatero-dorsal view (arrow indicates the curved and sharp subdistally sclerotized spine). Female: 64, Epigynum, ventral view. 65, Epigynum, dorsal view. 66, Epigynum, left lateral view. 67, Epigynum, frontal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs 58, 59, 62–67), 1 mm (Figs 56, 57, 60, 61)." pageId="20" pageNumber="40">Fig. 60</figureCitation>
); the long, curved and sharp sub-distally sclerotized spine on ventral part of embolus (arrow, 
<figureCitation box="[915,995,1726,1748]" captionStart="Figures 56–67" captionStartId="15.[144,234,1760,1779]" captionTargetBox="[270,1296,202,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-0@15.[263,1305,194,1730]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 56–67. Ixchela mendozai sp. nov. Male: 56, 57, Habitus, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. 58, Carapace and chelicerae, frontal view. 59, Chelicerae, frontal view. 60, 61, Left palp, retrolateral and prolateral views, respectively. 62, Chelicera, lateral view. 63, Bulb and embolus, prolatero-dorsal view (arrow indicates the curved and sharp subdistally sclerotized spine). Female: 64, Epigynum, ventral view. 65, Epigynum, dorsal view. 66, Epigynum, left lateral view. 67, Epigynum, frontal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs 58, 59, 62–67), 1 mm (Figs 56, 57, 60, 61)." pageId="20" pageNumber="40">Fig. 63</figureCitation>
); and the epigynum with three projections apically, the central markedly longer and curved, the lateral ones small and rounded (
<figureCitation box="[1255,1428,1787,1810]" captionStart="Figures 56–67" captionStartId="15.[144,234,1760,1779]" captionTargetBox="[270,1296,202,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-0@15.[263,1305,194,1730]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 56–67. Ixchela mendozai sp. nov. Male: 56, 57, Habitus, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. 58, Carapace and chelicerae, frontal view. 59, Chelicerae, frontal view. 60, 61, Left palp, retrolateral and prolateral views, respectively. 62, Chelicera, lateral view. 63, Bulb and embolus, prolatero-dorsal view (arrow indicates the curved and sharp subdistally sclerotized spine). Female: 64, Epigynum, ventral view. 65, Epigynum, dorsal view. 66, Epigynum, left lateral view. 67, Epigynum, frontal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs 58, 59, 62–67), 1 mm (Figs 56, 57, 60, 61)." pageId="20" pageNumber="40">Figs 64, 66, 67</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[826,1442,1850,1903]" lastBlockId="21.[144,759,198,1688]" lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="41" pageId="20" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis box="[826,1249,1850,1872]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="40">
Description: Male (
<typeStatus box="[1032,1130,1850,1871]" pageId="20" pageNumber="40">Holotype</typeStatus>
). Prosoma:
</emphasis>
Pale yellow, with three brown markings on each side (
<figureCitation box="[1260,1341,1881,1903]" captionStart="Figures 56–67" captionStartId="15.[144,234,1760,1779]" captionTargetBox="[270,1296,202,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-0@15.[263,1305,194,1730]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 56–67. Ixchela mendozai sp. nov. Male: 56, 57, Habitus, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. 58, Carapace and chelicerae, frontal view. 59, Chelicerae, frontal view. 60, 61, Left palp, retrolateral and prolateral views, respectively. 62, Chelicera, lateral view. 63, Bulb and embolus, prolatero-dorsal view (arrow indicates the curved and sharp subdistally sclerotized spine). Female: 64, Epigynum, ventral view. 65, Epigynum, dorsal view. 66, Epigynum, left lateral view. 67, Epigynum, frontal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs 58, 59, 62–67), 1 mm (Figs 56, 57, 60, 61)." pageId="20" pageNumber="40">Fig. 57</figureCitation>
). Ocular region pale yellow, with a brown longitudinal line projecting from AME (
<figureCitation box="[355,436,228,250]" captionStart="Figures 56–67" captionStartId="15.[144,234,1760,1779]" captionTargetBox="[270,1296,202,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-0@15.[263,1305,194,1730]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 56–67. Ixchela mendozai sp. nov. Male: 56, 57, Habitus, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. 58, Carapace and chelicerae, frontal view. 59, Chelicerae, frontal view. 60, 61, Left palp, retrolateral and prolateral views, respectively. 62, Chelicera, lateral view. 63, Bulb and embolus, prolatero-dorsal view (arrow indicates the curved and sharp subdistally sclerotized spine). Female: 64, Epigynum, ventral view. 65, Epigynum, dorsal view. 66, Epigynum, left lateral view. 67, Epigynum, frontal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs 58, 59, 62–67), 1 mm (Figs 56, 57, 60, 61)." pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Fig. 57</figureCitation>
). Fovea surrounded with an irregular, wide brown region, extending backward (
<figureCitation box="[151,229,289,312]" captionStart="Figures 56–67" captionStartId="15.[144,234,1760,1779]" captionTargetBox="[270,1296,202,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-0@15.[263,1305,194,1730]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 56–67. Ixchela mendozai sp. nov. Male: 56, 57, Habitus, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. 58, Carapace and chelicerae, frontal view. 59, Chelicerae, frontal view. 60, 61, Left palp, retrolateral and prolateral views, respectively. 62, Chelicera, lateral view. 63, Bulb and embolus, prolatero-dorsal view (arrow indicates the curved and sharp subdistally sclerotized spine). Female: 64, Epigynum, ventral view. 65, Epigynum, dorsal view. 66, Epigynum, left lateral view. 67, Epigynum, frontal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs 58, 59, 62–67), 1 mm (Figs 56, 57, 60, 61)." pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Fig. 57</figureCitation>
). Clypeus pale yellow, with a wide brown region near chelicerae (
<figureCitation box="[325,402,320,342]" captionStart="Figures 56–67" captionStartId="15.[144,234,1760,1779]" captionTargetBox="[270,1296,202,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-0@15.[263,1305,194,1730]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 56–67. Ixchela mendozai sp. nov. Male: 56, 57, Habitus, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. 58, Carapace and chelicerae, frontal view. 59, Chelicerae, frontal view. 60, 61, Left palp, retrolateral and prolateral views, respectively. 62, Chelicera, lateral view. 63, Bulb and embolus, prolatero-dorsal view (arrow indicates the curved and sharp subdistally sclerotized spine). Female: 64, Epigynum, ventral view. 65, Epigynum, dorsal view. 66, Epigynum, left lateral view. 67, Epigynum, frontal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs 58, 59, 62–67), 1 mm (Figs 56, 57, 60, 61)." pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Fig. 58</figureCitation>
). Chelicerae brown, pale around the SAC (
<figureCitation box="[259,340,351,373]" captionStart="Figures 56–67" captionStartId="15.[144,234,1760,1779]" captionTargetBox="[270,1296,202,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-0@15.[263,1305,194,1730]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 56–67. Ixchela mendozai sp. nov. Male: 56, 57, Habitus, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. 58, Carapace and chelicerae, frontal view. 59, Chelicerae, frontal view. 60, 61, Left palp, retrolateral and prolateral views, respectively. 62, Chelicera, lateral view. 63, Bulb and embolus, prolatero-dorsal view (arrow indicates the curved and sharp subdistally sclerotized spine). Female: 64, Epigynum, ventral view. 65, Epigynum, dorsal view. 66, Epigynum, left lateral view. 67, Epigynum, frontal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs 58, 59, 62–67), 1 mm (Figs 56, 57, 60, 61)." pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Fig. 59</figureCitation>
). Sternum pale yellow. Labium and endites brown; endites with retrolateral apophysis, which has a small subdistal protuberance. 
<emphasis box="[566,624,413,434]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Legs:</emphasis>
Coxae pale yellow, with small brown markings on retrolateral and prolateral parts. Trochanters pale yellow. Femora pale orange, with several brown rings throughout their length, one sub-distal ring dark brown, wide, very marked. Patellae brown. Tibiae pale orange, with several brown rings throughout their length, less visible than on femora. Metatarsi and tarsi orange, without colour rings. Legs with numerous oblique, long setae; with few short, vertical setae. 
<emphasis box="[429,582,687,708]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Opisthosoma:</emphasis>
Conical, longer than high, pale blue, with dorsal grey pattern (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 56–67" captionStartId="15.[144,234,1760,1779]" captionTargetBox="[270,1296,202,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-0@15.[263,1305,194,1730]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 56–67. Ixchela mendozai sp. nov. Male: 56, 57, Habitus, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. 58, Carapace and chelicerae, frontal view. 59, Chelicerae, frontal view. 60, 61, Left palp, retrolateral and prolateral views, respectively. 62, Chelicera, lateral view. 63, Bulb and embolus, prolatero-dorsal view (arrow indicates the curved and sharp subdistally sclerotized spine). Female: 64, Epigynum, ventral view. 65, Epigynum, dorsal view. 66, Epigynum, left lateral view. 67, Epigynum, frontal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs 58, 59, 62–67), 1 mm (Figs 56, 57, 60, 61)." pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Figs 56, 57</figureCitation>
). Gonopore plate oval. 
<emphasis box="[458,518,748,769]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Palp:</emphasis>
Femur pale yellow, conical, with several long setae ventrally; VAF conical, with sharp tip (
<figureCitation box="[337,471,810,832]" captionStart="Figures 56–67" captionStartId="15.[144,234,1760,1779]" captionTargetBox="[270,1296,202,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-0@15.[263,1305,194,1730]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 56–67. Ixchela mendozai sp. nov. Male: 56, 57, Habitus, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. 58, Carapace and chelicerae, frontal view. 59, Chelicerae, frontal view. 60, 61, Left palp, retrolateral and prolateral views, respectively. 62, Chelicera, lateral view. 63, Bulb and embolus, prolatero-dorsal view (arrow indicates the curved and sharp subdistally sclerotized spine). Female: 64, Epigynum, ventral view. 65, Epigynum, dorsal view. 66, Epigynum, left lateral view. 67, Epigynum, frontal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs 58, 59, 62–67), 1 mm (Figs 56, 57, 60, 61)." pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Figs 60, 61</figureCitation>
). Patella and tibia pale orange. Procursus brown, long and straight, with distal spine, thin and curved (
<figureCitation box="[408,531,871,893]" captionStart="Figures 56–67" captionStartId="15.[144,234,1760,1779]" captionTargetBox="[270,1296,202,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-0@15.[263,1305,194,1730]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 56–67. Ixchela mendozai sp. nov. Male: 56, 57, Habitus, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. 58, Carapace and chelicerae, frontal view. 59, Chelicerae, frontal view. 60, 61, Left palp, retrolateral and prolateral views, respectively. 62, Chelicera, lateral view. 63, Bulb and embolus, prolatero-dorsal view (arrow indicates the curved and sharp subdistally sclerotized spine). Female: 64, Epigynum, ventral view. 65, Epigynum, dorsal view. 66, Epigynum, left lateral view. 67, Epigynum, frontal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs 58, 59, 62–67), 1 mm (Figs 56, 57, 60, 61)." pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Figs 60, 61</figureCitation>
). VPP with 3–4 long setae (
<figureCitation box="[217,296,901,923]" captionStart="Figures 56–67" captionStartId="15.[144,234,1760,1779]" captionTargetBox="[270,1296,202,1724]" captionTargetId="figure-0@15.[263,1305,194,1730]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 56–67. Ixchela mendozai sp. nov. Male: 56, 57, Habitus, lateral and dorsal views, respectively. 58, Carapace and chelicerae, frontal view. 59, Chelicerae, frontal view. 60, 61, Left palp, retrolateral and prolateral views, respectively. 62, Chelicera, lateral view. 63, Bulb and embolus, prolatero-dorsal view (arrow indicates the curved and sharp subdistally sclerotized spine). Female: 64, Epigynum, ventral view. 65, Epigynum, dorsal view. 66, Epigynum, left lateral view. 67, Epigynum, frontal view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (Figs 58, 59, 62–67), 1 mm (Figs 56, 57, 60, 61)." pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Fig. 60</figureCitation>
). Embolus conical, dorsally with a curved spine (
