<paragraph blockId="21.[144,759,198,1688]" pageId="21" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis box="[168,390,1177,1198]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="41">
Female (
<typeStatus box="[271,377,1177,1198]" pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Paratype</typeStatus>
).
</emphasis>
Similar to the male, but with the following differences: 
<emphasis box="[446,551,1208,1229]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Prosoma:</emphasis>
The three brown markings larger and darker than on male. Clypeus with brown region longer than on male, forming an upside down, U-shaped area. 
<emphasis box="[393,450,1300,1321]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Legs:</emphasis>
The brown rings on femora and tibiae slightly more marked than on male. 
<taxonomicName authority=": Wider" authorityName="Wider" box="[144,344,1360,1382]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Epigynum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="21" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
