<paragraph blockId="21.[144,759,1727,1902]" pageId="21" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis box="[144,330,1727,1748]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Natural history:</emphasis>
The specimens were collected in an oak forest, the females on their irregular sheet webs among boulders on the ground; the male 
<typeStatus box="[612,707,1789,1811]" pageId="21" pageNumber="41">holotype</typeStatus>
was collected on an irregular sheet web in a corner inside a cabin, being the first specimen of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2000" box="[677,759,1850,1871]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Ixchela" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="21" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[677,759,1850,1871]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="41">Ixchela</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected inside a building.
</paragraph>
